Bring a large #pot{} of @salted water{} to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Finely dice @tomato{1}(finely diced). Peel and thinly slice @garlic{4%cloves}(thinly sliced). Pick @parsley{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped) leaves from stems.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with half the @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> TIP: If chicken starts to brown too quickly, lower heat to medium and cover pan with lid after flipping chicken.

Transfer to a #cutting board{} and tent with #foil{} to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1/2 cup pasta cooking water, then drain pasta.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in pan used for chicken over medium low. Add tomato, garlic, and @chili flakes{1%teaspoon}, and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> We used 1/2 tsp chili flakes; add a pinch more if you like things spicy.

Stir in @cream sauce base{4%ounce} and 1/4 cup reserved pasta cooking water. Bring to a simmer, then remove from heat. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Stir drained spaghetti, parsley, and @butter{1/2%tablespoon} into pan with sauce. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

> TIP: If needed, stir in more reserved cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is coated in a creamy sauce.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide pasta between #bowls{}; top with chicken and serve.